  "local_port": 49920,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What colleges should I apply for with a percentile ranging between 50-60 in CAT mocks?",
  "response": "Scoring between the 50th to 60th percentile in CAT mocks indicates that you may need to improve your preparation to aim for top-tier IIMs and other premier MBA colleges. However, there are still several good B-schools where you can apply with this percentile range. Here are some colleges that accept CAT scores in this range:\n\n### **Tier 2 B-Schools**\n1. **Great Lakes Institute of Management, Chennai and Gurgaon**  \n   - Accepts CAT, XAT, CMAT, and GMAT scores.  \n   - Known for its strong industry connections and one-year MBA program.  \n\n2. **IMT Ghaziabad (Institute of Management Technology)**  \n   - Accepts CAT, XAT, and GMAT scores.  \n   - Offers a good mix of academics and placements.  \n\n3. **IFMR Graduate School of Business, Krea University**  \n   - Accepts CAT, XAT, and GMAT scores.  \n   - Focuses on analytics and finance-oriented programs.  \n\n4. **Amity Business School, Noida**  \n   - Accepts CAT, XAT, GMAT, and MAT scores.  \n   - Offers a diverse range of specializations.  \n\n5. **Birla Institute of Management Technology (BIMTECH), Greater Noida**  \n   - Accepts CAT, XAT, GMAT, and CMAT scores.  \n   - Known for its strong alumni network.  \n\n6. **LBSIM (Lal Bahadur Shastri Institute of Management), Delhi**  \n   - Accepts CAT, XAT, and GMAT scores.  \n   - Focuses on practical learning and industry exposure.  \n\n7. **XIME (Xavier Institute of Management and Entrepreneurship), Bangalore and Kochi**  \n   - Accepts CAT, XAT, and CMAT scores.  \n   - Known for its entrepreneurial focus.  \n\n8. **SIMSREE (Sydenham Institute of Management), Mumbai**  \n   - Accepts CAT, CMAT, and MH-CET scores.  \n   - Offers affordable fees and decent placements.  \n\n### **Tier 3 B-Schools**\n1. **ICFAI Business School (IBS), Hyderabad and other campuses**  \n   - Accepts CAT, XAT, and IBSAT scores.  \n   - Known for its case study-based learning.  \n\n2. **NIBM (National Institute of Bank Management), Pune**  \n   - Accepts CAT, XAT, and CMAT scores.  \n   - Specializes in banking and finance.  \n\n3. **Christ University Institute of Management, Bangalore**  \n   - Accepts CAT, XAT, and CMAT scores.  \n   - Offers a variety of MBA specializations.  \n\n4. **Jaipuria Institute of Management, Lucknow, Noida, and Jaipur**  \n   - Accepts CAT, XAT, and CMAT scores.  \n   - Known for its decent placements and faculty.  \n\n### **Other Options**\n- **State-level B-Schools**: Many state government-run B-schools accept lower percentiles and offer affordable MBA programs with decent placements.  \n- **Private B-Schools**: Several private B-schools accept lower CAT scores but focus on practical exposure and placements.  \n\n### **Tips to Improve Your Chances**  \n1. **Improve Your Score**: Focus on strengthening your weaker sections (Quant, DILR, or VARC) to aim for a higher percentile.  \n2. **Apply to Other Exams**: Consider appearing for other MBA entrance exams like **XAT, SNAP, CMAT, MAT, or NMAT** to widen your options.  \n3. **Focus on Profile**: Highlight your academic achievements, work experience (if any), and extracurricular activities to make your application stand out.  \n4. **Prepare for GD-PI**: Work on your communication skills, general awareness, and mock interview practice to perform well in the selection rounds.  \n\nWith focused preparation and strategic applications, you can still secure admission to a good MBA program. Good luck!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
